1. text-align doesn't need prefixes because it was standardized before browser vendors started experimenting with prefixes.
2. margin doesn't need prefixes because every browser had margin implemented the same way
3. padding doesn't need prefixes because It was fundamental like margin
4. color Is the basic text styling from CSS1
5. background-color is a core styling property. It was fully standarized from the start.
6. font-size Typography basics were agreed upon early on.
7. border Border was part of the original box model spec which made it consistently implemented across browsers
8. display Basic layout modes like block and inline are foundational but newer values like flex need prefixes.